                'title' => '10 Tips to Prevent Heart Diseases-TheLifeCents',
                'slug' => '10-tips-to-prevent-heart-diseases',
                'excerpt' => 'Read our in-depth guide on 10 Tips to Prevent Heart Diseases-TheLifeCents.',
                'content' => '<p>Globally, cardiovascular diseases are some of the biggest killers to date and are observed to be causing deaths. However, it is important to appreciate the fact that many forms of the disease can be prevented through the alteration of specific behavior and making the correct decision. Applying these strategies will reduce the chances of contracting heart disease and improve heart health. Outlined here are ten rules for taking proper care of a heart.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Maintain a Balanced Diet</strong></h2>

<p>It should however be understood that diet has close ends in enhancing the overall well-being of the heart of an individual. Make sure your diet plans are a rich source of <a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/balanced-diet" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.healthline.com/health/balanced-diet">fruits, vegetables, whole grains</a>, and lean sources of proteins. Also, do not take foods containing trans fats, added sugar, and salt because they cause heart diseases. Choose fats that are good for you such as the fats in avocados, nuts, and olive oil. Little modifications in the food you take regularly greatly reduce the chances of heart problems in the future.</p>

<img src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfA0DuVPd0Zom3xOkRTLgFT3Nx6nkc1xTlh6L-kE10gVANAtclWS0sCtPdhO5maQY_MMHsCeU7u5blC4mVwuBmEXVbRadzHyUgbe8cUdWuyegYpuIQYRt8lXWg6jREnK_sEAX6OEw?key=LGwMT8ILSmrDnXkE2Tn4NrhL" alt="Prevention of Heart Diseases" style="width:535px;height:auto" /></figure>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Stay Physically Active</strong></h2>

<p>Taking care of the heart requires physical training to be performed severally. Minimum levels of exercise are 150 minutes per week of moderate-intensity aerobic activity or 75 minutes per week of vigorous physical activity. Therefore, through cycling, exercising, swimming, or even dancing blood flow is improved, high blood pressure will be brought under control and ideal body weights will be obtained. This simply means that physical exercise should be taken as -the best medicine, that individuals can use to prevent the development of heart diseases.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Quit Smoking</strong></h2>

<p>Of these, <a href="https://www.nhs.uk/better-health/quit-smoking/" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.nhs.uk/better-health/quit-smoking/">smoking is a causal risk factor</a> for heart disease. It breaks down the lining of blood vessels, decreases the ability of your blood to carry oxygen to your tissues, and speeds up the deposit of cholesterol and other substances on the walls of your arteries. It is also important to note that heart disease can be prevented through quitting smoking; your heart could be enhanced within weeks. If a person is a smoker, they must find people or organizations that will assist him or her to quit this dangerous habit.</p>

<img src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXd9m3y7CGOEZqLx9djhJQYrYcwKU5We9gcx-KYfmYDIazDxCBsWyvq2LM8kw0FAUkiugxM_vtgol3kp5jg43H6b10_3H0OLYRvx_5qBcczBJugg_lHrA0yO_K30fipJKnFrtdl20Q?key=LGwMT8ILSmrDnXkE2Tn4NrhL" alt="" style="width:550px;height:auto" /></figure>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Monitor Your Blood Pressure</strong></h2>

<p>Hypertension, referred to as high blood pressure, typically has no symptoms while raising your risk for heart disease to an alarming level. To keep your blood pressure in check ensure that you take your blood pressure test and keep the results within the normal range. A contrast to this is the following set of measures that form part and parcel of people’s lifestyles. Among them is the avoidance of the use of salt, exercise, and control of stress.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Manage Stress Effectively</strong></h2>

<p>Stress which becomes chronic has serious negative effects on the heart. It might cause overeating, smoking, or even overdrinking, something which can surely compromise the status of the cardiovascular health of any individual. Other forms of relaxation include breathing, meditation, yoga, going to bed, and and to family and friends.&nbsp; Tagging along with the relaxed state one comes to learn that recovery from such illnesses is well facilitated and heart-related complications prevented.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Maintain a Healthy Weight</strong></h2>

<p>Being overweight and obese are two of the most well-known risk factors for heart disease as they result in hypertension, high cholesterol levels, and diabetes. Be swimsuit-ready, slim down, and be conscious of the AHA-recommended proportion between the food you eat and the exercise you do. Make your goals achievable and measure your progress to keep you focused. A weight loss of even a few pounds can help tremendously in improving the health of the heart.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Limit Alcohol Consumption</strong></h2>

<p>Consumption of <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/heart-disease/in-depth/heart-disease-prevention/art-20046502" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/heart-disease/in-depth/heart-disease-prevention/art-20046502">large proportions of alcohol </a>tends to raise the blood pressure of the heart, and obesity is one of the causes of causes of heart diseases. If it is a beer or wine that is in doubt, then a glass of wine in a day for women and men and moderate amounts of beer for men not more than two in a day. If you are a hedonist they help you to cut down on Alcohol for the sake of the heart and that is if you are bothered about your health.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Get Quality Sleep</strong></h2>

<p>Make it a point to take between seven and eight hours of quality sleep each night. Mimic owls and get up and go to sleep at about the same time, have a bedtime ritual, and transform your bedroom into <a href="https://thelifecents.com/10-benefits-of-quality-sleep-thelifecents/" data-type="link" data-id="https://thelifecents.com/10-benefits-of-quality-sleep-thelifecents/">a sleep sanctuary</a>. There is an increased understanding that adequate sleep is very important for a healthy heart. Short sleep can make one develop conditions such as high blood pressure, obesity, and diabetes which are precursors to heart diseases.</p>

<img src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXcfzN0ACjZyaP-R3rK5Q7wDx_f3tVIrU-tc79GbibqYyboE_otAfctdwZfugtMyXCTBasXtTfJwqacPpDzDPtA93nxZcbym8MUpEatV1JeRBjmDmIeKtw751NE7_So3Kp-oCzG0?key=LGwMT8ILSmrDnXkE2Tn4NrhL" alt="" style="width:549px;height:auto" /></figure>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Control Cholesterol Levels</strong></h2>

<p>Cholesterol is dangerous because when it is in your bloodstream, there will be the formation of cholesterolemia which is a threat to arteries and puts you at real risk of getting a heart disease. Always ensure that you are often getting your lipid profile done to ensure that your cholesterol level is within the normal range. Eat slightly less of foods that contain high amounts of saturated fats and cholesterol and include in meals more foods that contain high amounts of fiber and omega-3 three fatty acids.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Stay Informed and Take Preventive Measures</strong></h2>

<p>It is therefore important that more information be spread and known about heart disease and its risk factors. It is also advised that you frequently visit your doctor to have an early diagnosis of any other problems. Share your risk of developing heart disease with your doctor and develop an individual prevention strategy. Being active is among the other best ways of avoiding heart disease.</p>

<h1 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h1>

<p>Heart disease is a <a href="https://thelifecents.com/5-ways-to-boost-your-lifestyle-thelifecents/" data-type="link" data-id="https://thelifecents.com/5-ways-to-boost-your-lifestyle-thelifecents/">severe illness</a> that is not a given and can be managed. You can greatly minimize your risk and enjoy a healthier and happier life if you follow these ten effective tips. As they say, the saying goes, the smallest slip turns the scale. It is advisable to commence with one or two of these habits and then proceed gradually to the others. The good news is that if you apply yourself to follow the guidelines closely you can avoid heart diseases and you can consume a healthier heart for many coming years.</p>',
