<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>1. Sensitive Skin-Friendly</strong></h2>

<p>Do you know what’s the biggest advantage of homemade laundry detergents? It is inherently free of chemicals that cause skin irritation and scent. Synthetic colours, preservatives, and fragrances used in the majority of over-the-counter detergents have the potential to cause allergic reactions. In children or those with sensitive skin, it might be more severe, much like eczema. Using the personalized recipe, you may mix each ingredient yourself, which is safe and hygienic.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>2. Cleaner Clothes Without Chemical Residue</strong></h2>

<p>Amazingly, most of the commercial alternatives would deposit the residue that develops into a layer on your clothes. Such buildup can reduce the lifespan of textiles and retain odours. It has been discovered that a <a href="https://www.thespruce.com/how-to-make-your-own-laundry-detergent-1387952">DIY laundry detergent recipe</a> using natural chemicals like baking soda and washing soda helps to completely rinse and break down the detergent. The outcome? Cleaner, Fresher clothes.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>3. Fewer Toxins in Your Home</strong></h2>

