<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>Concisely, when you hear yourself asking this question, <em>What is the most toxic laundry detergent</em>? then, in many cases, this is found right under your nose. One of the easiest solutions towards a toxin-free home is to abandon them in favour of a DIY attempt.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>4. Environmentally Friendly</strong></h2>

<p>The majority of the homemade solutions are biodegradable and contain no phosphates and sulfates, which are two of the biggest culprits in water pollution.</p>

<p>This is the difference it really makes:</p>

<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Biodegradable Ingredients</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>Cooking dishes are normally made using natural ingredients, which are eco-friendly and are not harmful to the environment.</p>

<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
