<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>You avoid phosphates, sulfates and chlorine that may contaminate water courses and kill aquatic life.</p>

<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Reduced Plastic Waste</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>Wash your own containers as opposed to throwing away plastic jugs once or twice a week.</p>

<p>You can safeguard your family by switching to a DIY laundry detergent recipe. And the plus point is that you will also be saving the Earth. That is a win-win.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>5. Save More Than You Think</strong></h2>

<p>If you\'re trying to cut back on everyday household expenses, starting with your laundry routine can make a big difference. You know the fact that homemade laundry detergent is cleaner and <a href="https://thelifecents.com/budget-warm-ways-to-transform-living-thelifecents/">budget-friendly</a> as well. A version can be developed at only pennies compared to commercial versions that may sell as high as 0.20 per load. It is a small change that could lead to an eventual big saving, particularly for a family with more than one child or an individual who does a lot of laundry.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>6. Cost-effective and Customizable</strong></h2>

<p>Talking of money! Commercial detergents (the so-called eco-friendly or fragrance-free laundry detergent) can be pricey. Yet the best homemade laundry detergent recipe has a cost of less than a cent per load. It takes no time, you can simply prepare a huge amount that can last you many months, and it would save you hundreds per year, yet the performance is not decreased.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>7. Easy to Make at Home</strong></h2>

