                'excerpt' => 'Read our in-depth guide on 2 Best Homemade Laundry Detergent Recipe Variants.',
                'content' => '<p>Tired of spending the hard-earned money on the commercially available detergents full of questionable ingredients? You are not alone. The effortless homemade laundry detergent recipe is in a marvelous second childhood with the lifestyle of being environment-conscious and economical becoming quite common.</p>

<p>The solution to how to make homemade laundry detergent<strong> </strong>is going round the world. It\'s not just about saving money anymore. People also want control over what goes into their clothes and onto their skin. So get your hands dirty and let\'s get started if you\'re prepared to give up store-bought items.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Why Use Laundry Detergent Made at Home?</strong></h2>

<p>Funny to think that making your own detergent is a few bucks, that it all boils down to this, it is just about living intentionally. Here\'s why more people are jumping on the DIY train:</p>

<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Cost-Saving Benefits: </strong></li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>The price of detergent in the supermarket can be quite steep, especially to big families. Following just a couple of cheap ingredients you can <a href="https://www.thespruce.com/homemade-detergent-test-8772447">make your own laundry detergent</a> that will last you months and will only cost you a few pennies a load.</p>

<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Eco-Friendly: </strong></li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>Do-it-yourself detergent gives you choice over every ingredient so you can avoid any useless chemicals, dyes or artificial fragrances. You can either leave it completely fragrance-free or use the essential oils that are natural to give it a slight odor. It also implies fewer packaging waste, which makes it a wise option of sustainable life.</p>

<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Gentle on Skin:</strong></li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>In case you or your family members are allergic or sensitive to skin issues then the change to fragrance-free laundry detergent which is homemade can make a huge difference. No longer rashes, inflammations, and itches on clothes!</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>What You’ll Need: Ingredients &amp; Tools</strong></h2>

<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Basic Ingredients:</strong></h3>

<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Baking Soda</strong> – Helps with deodorizing and softening water</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Washing Soda</strong> – Boosts cleaning power</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Castile Soap or Fels-Naptha Bar- </strong>A base natural cleansing</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Borax (optional) - </strong>Extra stain-fighting power (opts)</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Essential Oils</strong> (optional) – For those who want scented or fragrance-free laundry detergent</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>These are the main ingredients of any good homemade laundry detergent recipe<strong> </strong>and you can make them slightly different according to your personal taste or allergies.</p>

<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tools:</strong></h3>

