<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Instructions:</strong></h3>

<ol class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>In a big vessel, grated soap must be added to 4-6 cups of hot water that is heated literately.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Add in the remainder of the dry ingredients stirring until all have dissolved.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Take off the heat and allow cooling.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Put additional water and stir.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Pour into big containers (old bottles of washing detergents are good).</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>

<p>It is a low-impact liquid laundry detergent suitable to use with fabric and simple to prepare in large quantities. It is truly the <strong>best homemade laundry detergent recipe</strong> many say, due to its smooth texture and versatility.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Powder vs Liquid – Which One’s Better?</strong></h2>



