<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Customizing Your Detergent</strong></h2>

<p>Want to make it truly yours? Here’s how:</p>

<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Add Fragrance or Go Fragrance-Free:</strong> You can either add 10–15 drops of essential oil or leave it out for a fragrance-free laundry detergent.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li><strong>Skin Sensitivities?</strong> Stick to hypoallergenic soap bars.</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>

<p>Whether you\'re all about that lavender aroma or keeping it scentless, the recipe is fully adaptable.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Storage &amp; Usage Tips</strong></h2>

<p>Once your <a href="https://thelifecents.com/why-homemade-laundry-detergent-is-better/">homemade laundry detergent</a> is created, there is only adequate storage and use in order to make it effective and prolong its usage as much as possible. This is how to make the best out of your DIY:</p>

<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Best Storage Containers</strong></h3>

